An Optimization Problem
We want to find values for \(\alpha\) and \(\beta\) that minimize the sum of squared error.


sse &lt;- function(a,b){
  y &lt;- d$final # outcome
  x &lt;- d$midterm # explanatory variable

  predicted_y &lt;- a + b*x

  error &lt;- y - predicted_y

  return( sum(error^2) )
}
